## **srnap** - A suite of tools for ncRNA discovery, profiling and annotation from small RNA-Seq data ##

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The srnap subcommands include:

**Profiling and annotation tools** :

  profiles : ncRNA discovery and profiling from small RNA-Seq data

  annotate : ncRNA clustering, classification and annotation from profiles

**General help** :

  -h, --help :  Print this help menu

  -v, --version : What version of srnap are you using?

**Examples** :

          srnap profiles replicate1.bam replicate2.bam replicate3.bam output_dir
          srnap annotate output_dir/profiles.dat annotation.gtf output_dir

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
**Tool** : profiles

**Summary** : ncRNA discovery and profiling from small RNA-Seq data

**Usage** :

    srnap profiles [OPTIONS] replicate_1.bam ... replicate_n.bam output_folder

**Options**  :

           -l, --length      Length of the single-end reads
                             [ Default is 200 ]

           -c, --contigs     Profile definition
                             Format is <minlen:maxlen:spacing:minheight:trimming>, where:
                               - <minlen> is the minimum length of the contig. Contigs shorter than <minlen> are not reported. Must be > 5.
                               - <maxlen> is the maximum length of the contig. Contigs longer than <maxlen> are not reported. Must be > minlen.
                               - <spacing> is the maximum distance between contigs. Contigs separated by <spacing> or less bp are considered the same contig. Must be >= 0.
                               - <minheight> is the minimum number of piled-up reads. Contigs that have less than <minheight> piled-up reads are not reported. Must be > 0.
                               - <trimming> is the number of bases to trim. Bases in the 5' and 3' sites of the contig that have less than <trimming> piled-up reads are trimmed. Must be >= 0.
                             [ Default is 16:200:20:50:5 ]

           -r, --replicates  Replicates treatment
                             Format is <pool> | <mean> | <replicate:number>, where:
                               - <pool> : Profiles are built by pooling the reads of all the replicates.
                               - <mean> : Profiles are built by averaging the reads of all the replicates.
                               - <replicate:number> : Profiles are built by using only the reads of one replicate.
                             [ Default is pool ]

           -i, --ic          Irreproducibility control
                             Format is <method:cutoff> | <common> | <none>, where:
                               - <method> is the irreproducibility control method. Options are:
                                 - sere : Single-parameter quality control. (Schulze et al. BMC Genomics 2012)
                                 - idr  : Irreproducibility discovery rate. (Li et al. The Annals of Applied Statistics 2011)
                               - <cutoff> is the cutoff value. Contigs that have an irreproducibility score higher than <cutoff> are not reported.
                               - <common> : Contigs that do not overlap in all the replicates are not reported.
                               - <none>   : All contigs are reported.
                             [ Default is common ]

**Output** :

  output_folder/profiles.dat : List of ncRNA profiles with per-base heights

  output_folder/contigs.dat  : List of unfiltered contigs

**Examples** : 

    srnap profiles -c 20:200:20:50:5 -r pool -i sere:2 replicate1.bam replicate2.bam output_dir
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
**Tool** : annotate

**Summary** : ncRNA clustering, classification and annotation from profile data

**Usage** :

    srnap annotate [OPTIONS] profiles_file.dat output_folder

**Options** : 

            -a, --afile      Annotation file
                             Format is <annotation_file>, where:
                               - <annotation_file> is a BED file with annotated features
                             [ No default value ]

            -p, --pfile      Additional profiles file
                             Format is <species:profiles_file>, where:
                               - <species> is the name of the species where the profiles comes from. e.g. hsap.
                               - <profiles_file> is a profiles file
                             [ No default value ]

            -t, --threshold  Threshold for label propagation
                             Format is <threshold>, where:
                               - <threshold> is the threshold of the hierarchical clustering distance
                             [ Default is 0.80 ]

**Output** :

  output_folder/crosscorr.dat    : List of cross correlation coefficients between pairs of profiles

  output_folder/clusters.neWick  : List of clustered profiles

  output_folder/annotation.bed   : List of annotated features in BED file (only if annotation file is provided)

**Example** :

           srnap annotate -t 0.95 -a hsap_micrornas.bed profiles.dat output_dir
           srnap annotate -a hsap_micrornas.bed -p hsap:hsap_profiles.dat profiles.dat output_dir
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------